Undeterred, the user delved into the FreeBSD codebase, studying the existing Wi-Fi driver implementations and the underlying hardware specifications of their MacBook. Through meticulous research and hands-on experimentation, they managed to reverse-engineer the necessary components and develop a custom driver that seamlessly integrated with the FreeBSD kernel.

