  "article": "In a significant development for travelers, a new report has uncovered that the cheapest day to book flights has changed, potentially saving flyers up to 18% on airfare. This breaking news comes at a time when many are eager to plan their next getaway, making it crucial for consumers to stay informed on the latest trends.

The report, conducted by a leading travel analytics firm, analyzed millions of flight bookings to identify the optimal day of the week for securing the most affordable fares. Traditionally, Tuesday has been touted as the cheapest day to book flights, but the data now suggests a shift in this long-held assumption.

