\"We understand the concerns about potential conflicts of interest, but our primary goal is to improve the health and wellbeing of the population,\" said a spokesperson for the Department of Health and Social Care. \"These bonuses are just one part of a broader strategy to tackle the obesity epidemic, and we believe they will ultimately lead to better outcomes for patients.\"

As the debate continues, it remains to be seen how the £3,000 bonus scheme will impact prescribing patterns, patient outcomes, and the public's trust in the medical profession. Careful monitoring and transparent evaluation will be crucial to ensuring that any financial incentives do not compromise the integrity of the healthcare system.

